sentences: Youssef Soukouna (born 20 April 1981 in Goutte d'Or, Paris), better known by his stage name Sefyu (French pronunciation: ​[sɛfju], his first name in verlan), is a French rapper of Senegalese descent.

A member of the crews “NCC” (Natural Court Circuit –“ Natural Short Circuit”) and “G-Huit”, he started his ascent to fame by rapping with Rohff on his album La Fierté des nôtres, released in June 2004.
He performed publicly in 2001 at the Francofolies de la Rochelle.
In 2005, he released an EP entitled Molotov 4, which was produced by Kore et Skalp.
In April 2006, Sefyu released his first album, titled Qui Suis-je ?.
His 2007 song “”Lettre du Front” was released on R&B singer Kenza Farah's album Authentik.
On May 12, 2008, Sefyu released his second album, Suis-je le gardien de mon frère?
According to Planète Rap Magazine, 106,453 copies of Sefyu's second LP were sold in France in 2008.
On March 1, 2009, Sefyu went on to win the Victoire de la Musique Award, in the category “Revelation of the year”.

He emerged upon the hip-hop scene in the early 2000s to commercial and critical acclaim.
He went on to England to feature for London club Arsenal where he got an injury which eventually ended his playing days.
Authentik was released in the same year and as well garnered gold status.
Prior to its release, Sefyu made public the acclaimed singles “Mon Public”, “Molotov 4” and “Au pays du zahef” which contributed to the album's commercial success.
On March 1, 2009, Sefyu went on to win the Victoire de la Musique Award, in the category “Revelation of the year”.
